        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: detect linux slack desktop path",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add Linux Slack desktop config path discovery using XDG_CONFIG_HOME and ~/.config/Slack\n- keep the existing macOS desktop path behavior intact\n- document macOS and Linux desktop-mode config discovery\n\nFixes #52.\n\n## Validation\n- `gofmt -w internal/config/config.go internal/config/config_test.go`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `go test ./...`\n- `go test ./internal/config -run 'TestNormalizeAutoDetectsLinuxDesktopPath' -v`\n\n## Proof\nFocused desktop-path proof:\n\n```text\n=== RUN   TestNormalizeAutoDetectsLinuxDesktopPathFromXDGConfigHome\n--- PASS: TestNormalizeAutoDetectsLinuxDesktopPathFromXDGConfigHome\n=== RUN   TestNormalizeAutoDetectsLinuxDesktopPathFromHomeConfig\n--- PASS: TestNormalizeAutoDetectsLinuxDesktopPathFromHomeConfig\nPASS\nok      github.com/openclaw/slacrawl/internal/config\n```\n",
